  "text": "Tissue oxygen levels can be increased by the use of hyperbaric oxygen therapy, an approach that has been used to treat chronic hypoxia [CITATION_1] . We simulate this treatment at various times by returning the proliferation rate of fibroblasts and the rates of production of collagen and TGF-b to the corresponding values for the normal healing case. As seen in figure 5 , we find that the application of a treatment causes the ECM density to approach the corresponding value for the normal case. Furthermore, figure 6 shows that on applying treatment, the wound re-epithelializes at a rate closer to that of a normal wound.",
